dct_title_s: Bartlett's illustrated map of New York City,or, Stranger's guide showing the public buildings, places of amusement and its' various architectural features
dct_description_sm: Shows streets and landmarks in Manhattan south of 61st Street. "Entered according to Act of Congress in the year 1870 by G.H. Bartlett in the office of the Librarian of Congress in Washington." Originally issued in covers, 21 x 10 cm.
dct_publisher_sm: New York : G.H. Bartlett, c1870 (N[ew] Y[ork] : Major & Knapp Eng. Mfg. & Lith. Co.)
